    <key>CBReleaseWhatsNew</key>
    <string>Disabling a Local MCP connector now actually saves tokens. Previously the on/off switch only blocked tool calls — the tool schemas still shipped in every Claude Code system prompt. Now disabled connectors are skipped entirely at MCP server startup, so their schemas never reach tools/list. Expect ~1.5k–7.5k fewer context tokens per message depending on which connectors you turn off.
Toggling a connector auto-restarts your running `claude` CLI sessions (SIGINT → claude-watch resumes) so the new toolset takes effect immediately. Account credentials are not touched. cmux panes are skipped intentionally to avoid racing the cmux relauncher.
GitHub tool schemas slimmed ~38% — descriptions on self-explanatory fields dropped, enum hints compressed. Saves ~1,900 tokens per message whenever GitHub is enabled, with no change in tool behavior.</string>
